Board of Trustees (BoT), regional and state coordinators of the Buhari Campaign Organisation (BCO) have declared the ‘suspension’ of their National Coordinator, Alhaji Danladi Pasali as a nullity. A group of BCO members had purportedly suspended Pasali on September 28, 2020, and announced Malam Gidado Ibrahim as the new national coordinator. But reading a communique at the end of their meeting, the BoT chairman, Engr. Marcus Gundiri, said Alhaji Danladi  was “unconstitutional, illegal and was fraudulently made”. Board of Trustees (BoT), regional and state coordinators of the Buhari Campaign Organisation (BCO) have declared the ‘suspension’ of their National Coordinator, Alhaji Danladi Pasali as a nullity. A group of BCO members had purportedly suspended Pasali on September 28, 2020, and announced Malam Gidado Ibrahim as the new national coordinator. But reading a communique at the end of their meeting, the BoT chairman, Engr. Marcus Gundiri, said Alhaji Danladi  was “unconstitutional, illegal and was fraudulently made”.